%S A071713 0,14,1,98
%N A071713 a(n) = smallest value of |x^n + y^n + z^n| for x,y,z distinct nonzero integers.
%C A071713 If n is even, a(n)=1+2^n+3^n. Does a(5)=12 ?
%C A071713 The conjectured minimum of 12 for a(5) can be achieved by (x,y,z) = (13,16,-17). - _Stefan Steinerberger_, Dec 13 2007
%C A071713 Not only must x,y,z, be distinct, but also |x|, |y|, |z|. Otherwise take x = -y and z = 1; then for any odd n, a(n) = |x^n + (-x)^n + 1^n| = 1. - _Ryan Propper_, Feb 06 2008
